SIMPLE: double-entendre
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Double-entendre
<hw>Dou"ble-en*ten"dre</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>double</ets> double + <ets>entendre</ets> to mean. This is a
barbarous compound of French words. The true French equivalent is
<ets>double entente</ets>.]</ety> <def>A word or expression admitting of
a double interpretation, one of which is often obscure or
indelicate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Double-eyed</ent>⟦br⟧
